description:
Thrown in jail for a night for a crime he didn't commit, Tatsuki spirals closer to an emotional breakdown, and keeping his feelings to himself leaves him teetering perilously close to the edge. Meanwhile, Yuuto has a run-in with a part of his past that he's not quite ready to face. Then there's Akira, the sweet neighborhood kid who befriends Kotarou and seems completely and happily harmless. But since when is anything what it seems?

Act 8 & 9.
name: Vol. 4

description:
Into our cast waltzes another teenage pretty boy--and does *he* have a chip on his shoulder. Mercurial but charming, Kazuma Koutari instantly forms a bond with Kotarou and a *frightening* grudge with Tatsuki. But why? When he starts playing cruel emotional games on Tatsuki, our angst-ridden Oohira starts to lose faith in himself. Kotarou notices Tatsuki's new depression and grows more worried than he's ever been. He and Tatsuki are cousins and childhood friends, aren't they? Maybe now it's time to prove it!

Act 15 - 18.
name: Vol. 5

description:
Mysterious events are bringing the cast of characters closer together. Mio and Karen meet at last. A strange new manifestation of Kotarou's power surfaces, and Kotarou at last notices that his touches are...less than normal. Tatsuki receives an eerie message that puts him on edge. Knowing danger is on its way, will Tatsuki be ready when it arrives?

Act 19 - 22.
name: Vol. 6

description:
Everything is falling apart! After the horrifying events in Volume 6, Tatsuki and Kazumahave fallen out of touch with the world and are spiraling out of control. It's up to all the characters to intervene, including old acquaintances and new ones--yet even *this* isn't the end of their problems because new complications begin to appear. Can things get any worse?

Act 23 - 25.
name: Vol. 7

description:
The missing pieces of the puzzle brought to light by Tatsuki's kidnapping slowly fall into place. As usual, Tatsuki is trying to solve all problems by himself--but things aren't so simple this time. Now Kotarou must at last face his past, present, and future if he's to discover the secret of his power and the link it holds to Tatsuki. But at what cost? Prepare for the mind-bending conclusion of Hands Off!, and the fate of three friends blessed and cursed with ESP...

Act 26 - 28 (Final).
name: Vol. 8

description:
Flashing back to their high school days, this Hands Off side story unveils more about the psychic powers of Udou and Kiba. Udou has been using his skills in unsavory ways and Kiba is in deep denial about his powers until circumstances bring them together to deal with the problems going on around them. Cameo appearances of the Hands Off kids are included in the bonus material!

Act 1 - 4 & Don't Call Us Devils.
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Hands Off: Don't Call Us Angels

description:
After learning about Udou's power, Yari decides that he wants to get closer to Udou. Suspicious about the change in Yari's aura, Kiba follows the two and witnesses them showing off their "powers" by hurting random people on the street! Yari then locks Haruhi up in an abandoned cafe...and breaks Kiba's arm when he asks her about it. Will Kiba be able to save Haruhi...and himself?

Contains Act 6 - Act 8 (Final Act) and Don't Call Us Devils.
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: Hands Off: Don't Call Us Angels

description: One complication after another befalls Café Bonheur in this volume of Happy Café! A surprise visit from Ichiro’s little sister throws the café into confusion, and it’s not just because she seems to inexplicably hate Uru! And after a blackout traps Uru in his apartment, Shindo doesn’t sleep at all, causing him to fall ill the next day. Can the café survive the day without Shindo to keep everything in order? And can Shindo survive the day without Uru’s smile?
name: Vol. 4

description: In this volume of Happy Cafe, Ichiro comes to work at Bonheur, and makes some self-discoveries! Next, an old friend of Shindo’s stops by and gives us a rare glimpse into Shindo’s past. Then, a strange man (or woman?) stops by the café, and he seems to know Sou and Shindo... Finally, we discover just why Shindo loves making sweets.
name: Vol. 5

description: Following the destruction of Ceti Alpha VI the planet that was once a lush paradise begins to disintegrate before Khan's eyes, leaving Khan and his followers to struggle with the swift decline of their new home on Ceti Alpha V. In the face of decreasing resources and discontent from within, Khan continues to insist that Captain Kirk has not forgotten them and the Enterprise will come to the rescue.

volume.name: Star Trek: Khan Ruling in Hell

description:
Would you rather burn out or fade away? That's the question at the heart of this bold new series about a group of people who, for one reason or another, are at their wits' end until they're offered a chance to become superheroes. The catch? Their powers will kill them.

Writer Nick Spencer (Morning Glories) and artist CAFU (WAR OF THE SUPERMEN) present a fresh take on the classic comics property, starring a new batch of recruits brought in to take over the original agents' mantles and make some difficult choices of their own – all while dealing with global threats the rest of the DCU doesn't even know exist!
name: The High Road

description: Norma Balitzer is just your typical average foster mother...who happens to train her young wards to be hired killers! Dravis Trucker, her latest ward, has always yearned for a normal life. Now he's hoping to survive long enough to get his driver's license!

Dravis and Carrie give each other hope for a better life far away from the ugly and violent world they currently inhabit. But as the two foster children make plans to run away together, a ruthless killer has them in his crosshairs!

As Asgard celebrates victory, rumblings of Ragnarok near. What shocking revelation will the All-Father unveil to his chosen son? And what does Baron Zemo have in store for the gods? Jonathan Hickman (SHIELD) and Carlos Pacheco (Ultimate Avengers) rock out another thrilling tale of Thor's thunderous debut!

volume.name: Xotica - The art of Esteban Maroto

description: Two of Marvel's smallest heroes must join forces and get over one BIG elephant-in-the-room! Eric O'Grady once STOLE the Ant-Man suit from Hank Pym. But now, Eric is the only one who knows about a secret AIM plot to steal Pym's greatest invention! Can the two men get along long enough to save the soul of the former GOLIATH, Bill Foster? Tim Seeley, creator of “Hack/Slash” brings us the big story of the two smallest Avengers! And make sure you check out this adventure before the astonishing events of AVENGERS ACADEMY #7 next month!

name: Dennis the Menace in the Caribbean, Jamaica, Puerto Rico

volume.name: Dennis the Menace Bonus Magazine Series

description:
The ARTIFACTS lead-in series concludes!

The final battle for the mantle of the Angelus reaches its climax as Dani Baptiste takes on a foe who knows her every weakness, inside and out. Will Dani have to sacrifice everything dear to her, even her humanity, to survive?
name: Illumination, Part 6
Love Him... Love What He Does

description:
Julie Pezzini has led a rough life, including a stint in prison. But that's nothing compared to being the sister of an NYPD Detective who also happens to wield a powerful mystic weapon. Even Sara and the Witchblade might not be enough to keep Julie safe in Sara's world of supernatural threats!

Sara's job is on the line as her mental stability is being questioned. As she navigates the days after the horrible event that left both her sister dead and her daughter kidnapped, she finds herself standing over her sisters grave. Her world imploding around her, she finds the last person that should be in the graveyard, and theres answeres to be had of him.

name: Remembrance

description:
One Too Many Heartbreakers

I just couldn't help my attitude toward men! I'd meet a fellow and we'd hit it off! Then, just as soon as he'd start to get serious with me, I'd drop him like a hot potato! I never believed it was cruelty on my part! I just couldn't bear the thought of having a permanent relationship with any man! They called me the Heartbreaker, but I never planned it that way! Then when the time came for me to give my heart once and for all, my love went begging...

Jealousy

Jealousy is one of the greatest destroyers of love! It is a sign of immaturity...

Symphony of Love

From the first day Tod Stevens walked into my office, I realized that he had great talent! One of the finest young pianists I had ever heard! And even more than that, he was a warm, sweet, tender boy! Immediately I knew that my interest in him would not be limited to a personal manager's concern for her client! For I soon began to love Tod, although he never knew it! But when wealthy, attractive Ruth Bolter came along, I felt that Tod was slipping away from me...

Lovers' Spat

In the months that Bill and I had gone steady, we had never argued... never, that is, until the day before my sixteenth birthday...

Look For Love (Text Only Story)

My Sister My Enemy

Ever since we were little children, Rose and I were known as the "opposite sisters"! She was always pretty, charming, outgoing! I was the more subdued! Plain, dull, queit, and this carried over into the time of our growing up! Whenever Rose was with a handsome boy, I could be found with a good book! People thought I was happy that way! They never considered that I wanted to love, just like Rose... so it was natural that I would come to resent my sister, for she had the life I wanted!

Dear Diary

No Description

description: Dynamite is pleased to present the collected work of Grant Morrison and Mark Millar's incredible run on Vampirella. Over a decade ago two of the comic industry's most prolific writers of today joined together to craft what some consider Vampirella's finest run in her long history. Joining these two legendary creators are today's other top talents such as Amanda Connor, Jimmy Palmiotti, Brain Haberlin, Michael Bair, Kevin Nowlan, and more. This edition collects "Ascending Evil" from Vampirella Monthly #1-3, "Holly War" from Vampirella Monthly #4-6, "Blood Red Game" from the Vampirella 25th Anniversary Special, and "Cold Day in Hell" from Vampirella Strikes #6. This edition also collects interviews with Morrison, Millar, Connor, and Palmiotti. It all began right here for these creators and now it's collected for you in this beautiful trade paperback edition featuring a stunning cover by Jae Lee.
name: Grant Morrison and Mark Millar
